{"title_page": "Chromatica", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 studio album by Lady Gaga}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Chromatica\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Lady Gaga]]\n| cover        = Lady Gaga - Chromatica (Official Album Cover).png\n| alt          = \n| released     = May 29, 2020<!-- December 31 is just a placeholder date for digital music retailers -->\n| recorded     = January 2017\u2013 January 2020\n| studio       = * [[Electric Lady Studios]] (New York City)\n* [[Utility Muffin Research Kitchen]] ([[Hollywood Hills]])\n| genre        = \n| length       = \n| label        = * Streamline\n* [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| producer     = * [[BloodPop]]\n* [[Tchami]]\n* [[Boys Noize]]\n<!-- No co-producer or vocal producer here, see [[Template: Infobox album#producer]]. -->| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| prev_title   = [[A Star Is Born (2018 soundtrack)|A Star Is Born]]\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| misc         = {{Extra chronology<!---EXTRA CHRONOLOGY IS USEFUL WHEN DISCOGRAPHY COMES IN MANY FORMATS--->\n| artist       = Lady Gaga studio album\n| type         = studio\n| prev_title   = [[Joanne (album)|Joanne]]\n| prev_year    = 2016\n| title        = Chromatica\n| year         = 2020\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n}}{{Singles\n| name        = Chromatica\n| type        = studio\n| single1     = [[Stupid Love (Lady Gaga song)|Stupid Love]]\n| single1date = February 28, 2020\n }}\n}}\n\n'''''Chromatica'''''<ref name=\"Stereogum\">{{cite web |title=Lady Gaga\u2019s New Album Chromatica Is Out 4/10|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2075330/lady-gaga-new-album-chromatica/news/ |last=Rettig |first=James |date=March 2, 2020 |accessdate=March 2, 2020 |work=[[Stereogum]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302175023/https://www.stereogum.com/2075330/lady-gaga-new-album-chromatica/news/ |archive-date=March 2, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Fader\">{{cite web |title=Lady Gaga talks new album Chromatica: \u201cEarth is canceled. I live on Chromatica.\u201d |url=https://www.thefader.com/2020/03/02/lady-gaga-lg6-new-album-chromatica-stupid-love |last=Darvile |first=Jordan |date=March 2, 2020 |accessdate=March 2, 2020 |work=[[The Fader]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302175714/https://www.thefader.com/2020/03/02/lady-gaga-lg6-new-album-chromatica-stupid-love |archive-date=March 2, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> is the upcoming sixth studio album by American singer [[Lady Gaga]]. Originally scheduled for April 10, 2020, the album's release was delayed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]<!-- December 31 is just a placeholder date for digital music retailers -->. ''Chromatica'' will serve as a follow-up to Gaga's fifth studio album ''[[Joanne (album)|Joanne]]'' (2016), and her first full-length release since the [[A Star Is Born (2018 soundtrack)|soundtrack album]] for the film ''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]'' (2018). \n\nOn February 25, 2020, Gaga announced \"[[Stupid Love (Lady Gaga song)|Stupid Love]]\" as the album's [[lead single]], released on February 28, 2020.\n\n==Background==\nIn press interviews after it was announced she would embark on one final performance of her 2016 [[Dive Bar Tour (Lady Gaga)|Dive Bar Tour]], Gaga hinted new music would be performed and released during the new leg's stop. However, the Dive Bar Tour performance was later postponed indefinitely due to scheduling conflicts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/is-lady-gaga-las-vegas-dive-bar-tour-stop-postponed-1202492115/|title=Lady Gaga\u2019s Las Vegas Dive Bar Tour Stop Postponed|last=Aswad|first=Jem|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=July 11, 2017|access-date=August 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828233130/http://variety.com/2017/music/news/is-lady-gaga-las-vegas-dive-bar-tour-stop-postponed-1202492115/|archive-date=August 28, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Later, Gaga hinted the release of new music during the globe-crossing [[Joanne World Tour]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/lady-gaga-debut-new-music-on-tour-2099471|title=Lady Gaga to debut new music on tour|last=Butler|first=Will|publisher=[[NME]]|date=July 6, 2017|access-date=July 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708063859/http://www.nme.com/news/lady-gaga-debut-new-music-on-tour-2099471|archive-date=July 8, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> however it was later revealed by Gaga in an interview with ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' that due to the constraints of the tour production, specifically the strictly-scheduled synchronization of its various technologies with the performances, there most likely will not be any new material performed on the Joanne World Tour, let alone any deviation from the structure of the show itself.<ref name=\"ew82017\">{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/music/2017/08/29/lady-gaga-next-album-lg6-interview/|title=Lady Gaga is working on a new album: 'I have a lot of ideas'|last=Nolfi|first=Joey|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=August 29, 2017|access-date=August 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316045638/http://ew.com/music/2017/08/29/lady-gaga-next-album-lg6-interview/|archive-date=March 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> It was also revealed in the same interview that production had begun on the follow up to ''[[Joanne (album)|Joanne]]'', with Gaga offering that the album was still in the initial writing stage.<ref name=\"ew82017\"/>\n\n==Writing and recording==\nIn the first seven months of 2018, Gaga was seen at various recording studios in and around [[Los Angeles]] and [[New York City]]. The earlier recording sessions have been attributed to [[post-production]] work for the [[A Star Is Born (2018 soundtrack)|soundtrack]] to [[Bradley Cooper]]'s ''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]'', a remake of the [[A Star Is Born (1937 film)|1937 film of the same name]] in which she has top billing. The later recording sessions have mostly been attributed to further production for ''Chromatica''. Producer [[BloodPop]], who had co-produced every song on the standard edition of Gaga's previous studio album ''Joanne'' (2016), shared on various social media platforms that he and Gaga had been recording at the singer's Malibu estate with German electronic music producer [[Boys Noize]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8356693/lady-gaga-boys-noize |title=Lady Gaga & Boys Noize Are Working Together in the Studio|last=Bein|first=Kat|date=April 19, 2018|accessdate=May 8, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420182625/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8356693/lady-gaga-boys-noize |archivedate=April 20, 2018|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> BloodPop continued to post similar updates through the entirety of 2019 and January 2020, indicating production had continued for nearly three years. In July 2018, experimental electronic music producer [[Sophie (musician)|Sophie]] confirmed that she had contributed production work for the upcoming project but was unaware if her collaboration would make the final cut.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Ting |first1=Jasmine |title=SOPHIE Confirms Lady Gaga Collab |magazine=Paper |date=July 8, 2018 |url=http://www.papermag.com/sophie-confirms-lady-gaga-collab-2584857276.html |accessdate=August 10, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709001833/http://www.papermag.com/sophie-confirms-lady-gaga-collab-2584857276.html |archivedate=July 9, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with [[Beats 1|Beats 1's]] [[Zane Lowe]], Gaga confirmed the album will be a dance record, saying \"We are definitely dancing\u2026 I put all my heart, all my pain, all my messages from the other realm that I hear of\u2026 what they tell me to tell the world and I put it into music that I believe to be so fun and you know, energetically really pure. I want people to dance and feel happy. I would like to put out music that a big chunk of the world will hear, and it will become a part of their daily lives and make them happy every single day.\"<ref name=\"Beats1\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/post/sa.e8ad7cc0-59c3-11ea-b990-4d970530bffb|title=Lady Gaga on \"Stupid Love\"|3=|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020|website=New Music Daily with Zane Lowe|publisher=Apple Inc.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229041344/https://music.apple.com/us/post/sa.e8ad7cc0-59c3-11ea-b990-4d970530bffb|archive-date=February 29, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> She divulged how her intuition had evolved since the production of her last album, especially with the \"real\" and \"honest\" nature of this record's production virtually halting her inclination to second guess her creative output.<ref name=\"Beats1\"/> Gaga also went into great detail about how the collaborative process of creating the album helped her overcome her internal struggles:\n{{Quote|text=We made a lot of the record in my studio house. So I have a house where it's [[Frank Zappa|Frank Zappa's]] old [[Utility Muffin Research Kitchen|studio]], it's a live room, it's a big studio, it's beautiful. And I would be upstairs on the porch, outside the kitchen, and Bloodpop would come up and he'd go, 'Okay, come on, that's enough, off the porch,' and I would cry and I would say, 'I'm miserable, I'm sad, I\u2019m depressed,' and he'd go, 'I know, and we're gonna go make some music now. And then I'd go downstairs and I would write. This album is such a display of not only how you can reframe the way that you view the world, but I promise and I hope, that the love that was around me in the process of making this album is something that other people feel, that they know that artistically, like, you know how producers are, if one guy\u2019s working on it, or one girl\u2019s working on it, they don\u2019t want anyone else to work on it, they don\u2019t wanna share, they, everybody gets cocky, there was none of that. These records got passed around to so many different people, there were so many different iterations of these songs because we all wanted it to be perfect and literally nobody cared who put their fingerprints on it, as long as it was the dopest thing that we could give to the world and that it was meaningful, authentic, and completely me.<ref name=\"Beats1\"/>}}\n\nIn an interview with ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'' released in March 2020, Gaga talked at length about numerous topics, including the recording process for ''Chromatica'', and confirmed that BloodPop was the \"center\" and her \"nucleus\" of production while creating the album and that he had a hand in the creation of every track.<ref name=\"Paper1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/lady-gaga-chromatica-2645479910.html |title=Lady Gaga: Life on Chromatica |last=Moran |first=Justin |date=March 16, 2020 |accessdate=March 20, 2020 |work=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]}}</ref> It was also confirmed in the same interview that Gaga worked with a wide array of producers and musicians, such as [[Burns (musician)|Burns]], [[Axwell]] of [[Swedish House Mafia]], [[Tchami]], Benjamin Rice, and [[Rami Yacoub]], to create an album described as an \"[[electronic music|electronic]] [[tapestry]]\u201d by the interviewer.<ref name=\"Paper1\"/> In discussing the large collaborative atmosphere that enveloped the album's production, she said, \"It's easy to go into a computer and find a cool loop, but the producers I work with don't work this way. When they're inspired, they embroider things.\"<ref name=\"Paper1\"/> Gaga disclosed that she had collaborated with a \"fellow female pop star who [had similarly experienced] immense trauma while in the public eye\" and went into depth about the genesis of their song, which she describes as a \"celebration of all the tears\": \"I sat with her and we talked about our lives. It's two women having a conversation about how to keep going and how to be grateful for what you do.\"<ref name=\"Paper1\"/>\n\n==Title and packaging==\nTalking about the album's title, Gaga stated \"I live on Chromatica, that is where I live. I went into my frame. I found earth, I deleted it. Earth is canceled. I live on Chromatica.\" A temporary cover art was released along with the album preorder, showcasing a symbol which \"has a [[sine wave]] in it, which is the mathematical symbol for sound. And, for me, sound is what healed me in my life period, and it healed me again making this record, and that is really what Chromatica is all about.\"<ref name=\"Pitchfork2020\">{{cite web |title=Lady Gaga Announces New Album Chromatica |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/lady-gaga-announces-new-album-chromatica/ |last1=Strauss |first1=Matthew |last2=Bloom |first2=Matthew |date=March 2, 2020 |accessdate=March 2, 2020 |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302173858/https://pitchfork.com/news/lady-gaga-announces-new-album-chromatica/ |archive-date=March 2, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nGaga also confirmed how the concept of the planet Chromatica came about, saying: <blockquote>BloodPop brought it up, and we talked about how Chromatica was essentially on its own when you first look at it, it seems to be about colors and all the different colors and also music is made of a [[chromatic scale]], you know? So it's all the colors, all the sounds, you know, so we, we're talking about inclusivity and life and also a lot of what we see around us and what we're experiencing is math, which is very much like music and sound is math as well. So we talked about that, and then I sort of went back and I said, 'OK, well, yeah, it's inclusivity but it's really a way of thinking,' you know, it's not just, 'Oh, Chromatica, we're being inclusive with all the colors, all the people,' and when I say, 'All the colors, all the people'  I mean way more than we could possibly fathom.\"<ref name=\"Pitchfork2020\"/></blockquote>\n\nOn April 5, 2020, the album's official cover was revealed.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=ladygaga |number=1246905802952077312 |title=#Chromatica \u2694\ufe0f\ud83d\udc932020 |date=April 5, 2020 |accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> It shows the singer with \"cotton candy pink\" hair, wearing a \"metallic bodysuit with spikes and studs sticking out of it\", \"a pair of platform boots with a tusk and a knife for its heels\" and a \"shoulder-to-fingertip sleeve covered in spikes\" on one of her hands. She is attached to a large metal grate illuminated by \"hot pink neon\" light.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daly |first1=Rhian |title=Lady Gaga shares first look at 'Chromatica' album artwork |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-shares-first-look-at-chromatica-album-artwork-2641331 |website=[[NME]] |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |date=April 6, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Lady Gaga Unveils The Mind-Boggling Cover Of 'Chromatica' |url=https://www.idolator.com/7908903/lady-gaga-unveils-the-mind-boggling-cover-of-chromatica?view-all&adblock=1&chrome=1 |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |date=April 5, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hughes |first1=Hilary |title=Lady Gaga Flexes Her 'Chromatica' Claws in New Album Cover Art: See the Pics |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9351515/lady-gaga-chromatica-album-cover-art |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Release and promotion==\nIn response to tabloid reports saying she might be pregnant, Gaga tweeted on March 12, 2019, \"Rumors I'm pregnant? Yeah, I'm pregnant with #LG6.\"<ref>{{cite tweet |user=ladygaga |number=1105619299572432897 |date=March 12, 2019 |title=Rumors I\u2019m pregnant? Yeah, I\u2019m pregnant with #LG6 }}</ref><ref name=\"LG6\">{{cite web|last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Lady Gaga Confirms That She\u2019s Hard At Work On \u2018LG6\u2019 |work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=March 13, 2019 |url=https://www.idolator.com/7721307/lady-gaga-new-album-2019-lg6 |accessdate=March 18, 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Maicki |first1=Salvatore |title=Lady Gaga says she\u2019s pregnant with her new album |work=[[The Fader]] |date=March 12, 2019 |url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/03/12/lady-gaga-new-album-lg6-rumors-rihanna-instagram |accessdate=March 18, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330062430/https://www.thefader.com/2019/03/12/lady-gaga-new-album-lg6-rumors-rihanna-instagram |archive-date=March 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Several news outlets speculated the tweet alluded to a release within a nine month window, the typical span of a human pregnancy, but the anniversary has since come and gone, proving the theory to be false.<ref name=\"LG6\"/> In October 2019, she jokingly announced via Twitter that the album would be called ''Adele'' after the [[Adele|English singer-songwriter of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.avclub.com/move-over-joanne-cause-lady-gaga-says-her-next-albums-1838678026 |last=Vargas |first=Alani |date=October 1, 2019 |accessdate=November 10, 2019 |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |title=Move Over ''Joanne'', 'Cause Lady Gaga Says her Next Album's Called...''Adele'' |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107094014/https://news.avclub.com/move-over-joanne-cause-lady-gaga-says-her-next-albums-1838678026 |archive-date=November 7, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/10/lady-gagas-sixth-album-will-be-called-adele.html|title=Trolling in the Deep: Lady Gaga's Calling Her Next Album ADELE|website=[[Vulture (website)|Vulture]]|last=Alter|first=Rebecca|date=October 1, 2019|accessdate=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122025553/https://www.vulture.com/2019/10/lady-gagas-sixth-album-will-be-called-adele.html|archive-date=November 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-naming-next-album-adele-2552838|title=Is Lady Gaga naming her next album 'ADELE'?|work=[[NME]]|last=Clarke|first=Patrick|date=October 1, 2019|accessdate=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002200058/https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-naming-next-album-adele-2552838|archive-date=October 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2020, several news outlets reported that the album's lead single was scheduled to be released in early February, with the album's release following soon afterwards.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Close |first1=Paris |title=Lady Gaga Will Reportedly Release A New Song In February |work=[[iHeartRadio]] |url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2020-01-19-lady-gaga-will-reportedly-release-a-new-song-in-february/ |date=January 19, 2020 |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200120015830/https://www.iheart.com/content/2020-01-19-lady-gaga-will-reportedly-release-a-new-song-in-february/ |archive-date=January 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n\nOn March 2, 2020, Gaga announced that the album is named ''Chromatica'' and that it will be released on April 10, 2020. The pre-order for the album was made available with the announcement.<ref name=\"Stereogum\"/><ref name=\"Fader\"/> On March 24, Gaga announced in a statement on Instagram and other platforms that the release would be postponed until later that year due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9341556/lady-gaga-pushes-back-chromatica-album |last1=Hughes |first1=Hilary |title=Lady Gaga Pushes Back 'Chromatica' Album Due to 'All That Is Going On' With Global Pandemic |date=March 24, 2020 |access-date=March 25, 2020 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref>\n<!-- Don\u2019t add the tour here, create a separate page for \"The Chromatica Ball\". -->\n\n===Singles===\n\"[[Stupid Love (Lady Gaga song)|Stupid Love]]\" was released as the album's [[lead single]] on February 28, 2020.<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/lady-gaga-stupid-love-new-single-leak-1203474728/|title=Lady Gaga\u2019s New Single, \u2018Stupid Love,\u2019 Is Dropping Friday|last=Stedman|first=Alex|last2=|first2=|date=2020-02-25|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225171654/https://variety.com/2020/music/news/lady-gaga-stupid-love-new-single-leak-1203474728/|archive-date=February 25, 2020|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The accompanying music video was directed by [[Daniel Askill]] and was released alongside the song on February 28.\n\n===Tour===\n{{main|The Chromatica Ball}}\nOn March 5, 2020, Gaga announced she would embark on [[The Chromatica Ball]] tour to support the album.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9328728/lady-gaga-sets-chromatica-stadium-tour |title=Lady Gaga Sets &#39;Chromatica&#39; Stadium Tour |date=March 5, 2020 |access-date=March 5, 2020 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref name=\"RollingStone\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/lady-gaga-chromatica-ball-tour-962547/ |title=Lady Gaga Announces Six-City The Chromatica Ball Summer Tour |date=March 5, 2020 |access-date=March 5, 2020 |website=[[Rolling Stone]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Variety2\">{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/lady-gaga-chromatica-ball-tour-dates-1203524722/ |title=Lady Gaga Unveils \u2018Chromatica Ball\u2019 Tour Dates |date=March 5, 2020 |access-date=March 5, 2020 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> The six-date trek is scheduled to begin on July 24, 2020, in [[Saint-Denis, Seine-Saint-Denis|Saint-Denis]], France and end on August 19, 2020, in [[East Rutherford, New Jersey|East Rutherford]], United States.<ref name=\"Gaga.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ladygaga.com/thechromaticaball|title=LADY GAGA {{!}} THE CHROMATICA BALL|date=March 5, 2020|website=LADY GAGA|language=en|access-date=March 5, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"RollingStone\"/><ref name=\"Variety2\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\nIt is revealed the album will contain 16 tracks in total, while the [[Target Corporation|Target]]-exclusive deluxe edition will contain three additional tracks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/chromatica/1500951604|title=Chromatica by Lady Gaga on Apple Music|date=April 10, 2020|author=Lady Gaga|website=music.apple.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.target.com/p/lady-gaga-chromatica-target-exclusive-cd/-/A-79694377|title=Lady Gaga - Chromatica (Target Exclusive, CD)|website=www.target.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| total_length = \n| title1 = \n| writer1 = \n| extra1 = \n| length1 = \n| title2 = \n| writer2 = \n| extra2 = \n| length2 = \n| title3 = [[Stupid Love (Lady Gaga song)|Stupid Love]]\n| writer3 = {{hlist|[[Lady Gaga|Stefani Germanotta]]|[[Max Martin]]|Ely Weisfeld|[[BloodPop|Michael Tucker]]|[[Tchami|Martin Bresso]]}}\n| extra3 = {{hlist|[[BloodPop]]|[[Tchami]]|Martin{{ref|b|[b]}}|Ben Rice{{ref|c|[c]}}}}\n| length3 = 3:13\n| title4 =  \n| writer4= \n| extra4= \n| title5 =\n| writer5 =\n| extra5 =\n| length5 = \n| title6 = \n| writer6 = \n| extra6 = \n| length6 = \n| title7 = \n| writer7 = \n| extra7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| writer8 = \n| extra8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| writer9 = \n| extra9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| writer10 = \n| extra10 = \n| length10 = \n| title11 = \n| writer11 = \n| extra11 = \n| length11 = \n| title12 = \n| writer12 = \n| extra12 = \n| length12 = \n| title13 = \n| writer13 = \n| extra13 = \n| length13 = \n| title14 = \n| writer14 = \n| extra14 = \n| length14 = \n| title15 = \n| writer15 = \n| extra15 = \n| length15 = \n| title16 = \n| writer16 = \n| extra16 = \n| length16 = \n| all_writing = \n}}\n\n===Notes===\n* <sup>{{note|b|[b]}}</sup> signifies a co-[[record producer|producer]].\n* <sup>{{note|c|[c]}}</sup> signifies a vocal producer.\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Country\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Version\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| Various\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Media streaming|streaming]]|[[Phonograph record|vinyl]]|[[Cassette tape|cassette]]}}\n| Standard\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://shopuk.ladygaga.com/*/Music/Chromatica-Cassette-1/6EQH0REG000|title=Chromatica Cassette 1|publisher=Lady Gaga Store|access-date=March 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302200342/https://shopuk.ladygaga.com/*/Music/Chromatica-Cassette-1/6EQH0REG000|archive-date=March 2, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://shopuk.ladygaga.com/*/Music/Chromatica-Standard-Vinyl/6EQF0REG000|title=Chromatica Standard Vinyl|publisher=Lady Gaga Store|access-date=March 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302200340/https://shopuk.ladygaga.com/*/Music/Chromatica-Standard-Vinyl/6EQF0REG000|archive-date=March 2, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Compact disc|CD]]\n| {{hlist|Standard|deluxe}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://shopuk.ladygaga.com/*/Music/Chromatica-Standard-CD/6EQE0REG000|title=Chromatica Standard CD|publisher=Lady Gaga Store|access-date=March 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302200343/https://shopuk.ladygaga.com/*/Music/Chromatica-Standard-CD/6EQE0REG000|archive-date=March 2, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://shopuk.ladygaga.com/*/Music/Chromatica-Deluxe-CD/6EQI0REG000|title=Chromatica Deluxe CD|publisher=Lady Gaga Store|access-date=March 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302200349/https://shopuk.ladygaga.com/*/Music/Chromatica-Deluxe-CD/6EQI0REG000|archive-date=March 2, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Lady Gaga}}\n\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by BloodPop]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Boys Noize]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Nick Monson]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Sophie (musician)]]\n[[Category:Interscope Records albums]]\n[[Category:Lady Gaga albums]]\n[[Category:Upcoming albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 studio album by Lady Gaga}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Chromatica\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Lady Gaga]]\n| cover        = Lady Gaga - Chromatica (Official Album Cover).png\n| alt          = \n| released     = 2020<!-- December 31 is just a placeholder date for digital music retailers -->\n| recorded     = 2017\u20132020\n| studio       = \n* [[Electric Lady Studios]] (New York City)\n* [[Utility Muffin Research Kitchen]] ([[Hollywood Hills]])\n| genre        = \n| length       = \n| label        =\n* Streamline\n* [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| producer     =\n* [[BloodPop]]\n* [[Tchami]]\n* [[Boys Noize]]\n<!-- No co-producer or vocal producer here, see [[Template: Infobox album#producer]]. -->\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| prev_title = [[A Star Is Born (2018 soundtrack)|A Star Is Born]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| misc         = {{Extra chronology<!---EXTRA CHRONOLOGY IS USEFUL WHEN DISCOGRAPHY COMES IN MANY FORMATS--->\n| artist       = Lady Gaga studio album\n| type         = studio\n| prev_title   = [[Joanne (album)|Joanne]]\n| prev_year    = 2016\n| title        = Chromatica\n| year         = 2020\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n}}{{Singles\n| name        = Chromatica\n| type        = studio\n| single1     = [[Stupid Love (Lady Gaga song)|Stupid Love]]\n| single1date = February 28, 2020\n }}\n}}\n\n'''''Chromatica'''''<ref name=\"Stereogum\">{{cite web |title=Lady Gaga\u2019s New Album Chromatica Is Out 4/10|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2075330/lady-gaga-new-album-chromatica/news/ |last=Rettig |first=James |date=March 2, 2020 |accessdate=March 2, 2020 |work=[[Stereogum]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302175023/https://www.stereogum.com/2075330/lady-gaga-new-album-chromatica/news/ |archive-date=March 2, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Fader\">{{cite web |title=Lady Gaga talks new album Chromatica: \u201cEarth is canceled. I live on Chromatica.\u201d |url=https://www.thefader.com/2020/03/02/lady-gaga-lg6-new-album-chromatica-stupid-love |last=Darvile |first=Jordan |date=March 2, 2020 |accessdate=March 2, 2020 |work=[[The Fader]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302175714/https://www.thefader.com/2020/03/02/lady-gaga-lg6-new-album-chromatica-stupid-love |archive-date=March 2, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> is the upcoming sixth studio album by American singer [[Lady Gaga]]. Originally scheduled for April 10, 2020, the album's release was delayed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]<!-- December 31 is just a placeholder date for digital music retailers -->. ''Chromatica'' will serve as a follow-up to Gaga's fifth studio album ''[[Joanne (album)|Joanne]]'' (2016), and her first full-length release since the [[A Star Is Born (2018 soundtrack)|soundtrack album]] for the film ''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]'' (2018). \n\nOn February 25, 2020, Gaga announced \"[[Stupid Love (Lady Gaga song)|Stupid Love]]\" as the album's [[lead single]], released on February 28, 2020.\n\n==Background==\nIn press interviews after it was announced she would embark on one final performance of her 2016 [[Dive Bar Tour (Lady Gaga)|Dive Bar Tour]], Gaga hinted new music would be performed and released during the new leg's stop. However, the Dive Bar Tour performance was later postponed indefinitely due to scheduling conflicts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/is-lady-gaga-las-vegas-dive-bar-tour-stop-postponed-1202492115/|title=Lady Gaga\u2019s Las Vegas Dive Bar Tour Stop Postponed|last=Aswad|first=Jem|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=July 11, 2017|access-date=August 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828233130/http://variety.com/2017/music/news/is-lady-gaga-las-vegas-dive-bar-tour-stop-postponed-1202492115/|archive-date=August 28, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Later, Gaga hinted the release of new music during the globe-crossing [[Joanne World Tour]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/lady-gaga-debut-new-music-on-tour-2099471|title=Lady Gaga to debut new music on tour|last=Butler|first=Will|publisher=[[NME]]|date=July 6, 2017|access-date=July 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708063859/http://www.nme.com/news/lady-gaga-debut-new-music-on-tour-2099471|archive-date=July 8, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> however it was later revealed by Gaga in an interview with ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' that due to the constraints of the tour production, specifically the strictly-scheduled synchronization of its various technologies with the performances, there most likely will not be any new material performed on the Joanne World Tour, let alone any deviation from the structure of the show itself.<ref name=\"ew82017\">{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/music/2017/08/29/lady-gaga-next-album-lg6-interview/|title=Lady Gaga is working on a new album: 'I have a lot of ideas'|last=Nolfi|first=Joey|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=August 29, 2017|access-date=August 29, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316045638/http://ew.com/music/2017/08/29/lady-gaga-next-album-lg6-interview/|archive-date=March 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> It was also revealed in the same interview that production had begun on the follow up to ''[[Joanne (album)|Joanne]]'', with Gaga offering that the album was still in the initial writing stage.<ref name=\"ew82017\"/>\n\n==Writing and recording==\nIn the first seven months of 2018, Gaga was seen at various recording studios in and around [[Los Angeles]] and [[New York City]]. The earlier recording sessions have been attributed to [[post-production]] work for the [[A Star Is Born (2018 soundtrack)|soundtrack]] to [[Bradley Cooper]]'s ''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]'', a remake of the [[A Star Is Born (1937 film)|1937 film of the same name]] in which she has top billing. The later recording sessions have mostly been attributed to further production for ''Chromatica''. Producer [[BloodPop]], who had co-produced every song on the standard edition of Gaga's previous studio album ''Joanne'' (2016), shared on various social media platforms that he and Gaga had been recording at the singer's Malibu estate with German electronic music producer [[Boys Noize]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8356693/lady-gaga-boys-noize |title=Lady Gaga & Boys Noize Are Working Together in the Studio|last=Bein|first=Kat|date=April 19, 2018|accessdate=May 8, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420182625/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8356693/lady-gaga-boys-noize |archivedate=April 20, 2018|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> BloodPop continued to post similar updates through the entirety of 2019 and January 2020, indicating production had continued for nearly three years. In July 2018, experimental electronic music producer [[Sophie (musician)|Sophie]] confirmed that she had contributed production work for the upcoming project but was unaware if her collaboration would make the final cut.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Ting |first1=Jasmine |title=SOPHIE Confirms Lady Gaga Collab |magazine=Paper |date=July 8, 2018 |url=http://www.papermag.com/sophie-confirms-lady-gaga-collab-2584857276.html |accessdate=August 10, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709001833/http://www.papermag.com/sophie-confirms-lady-gaga-collab-2584857276.html |archivedate=July 9, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with [[Beats 1|Beats 1's]] [[Zane Lowe]], Gaga confirmed the album will be a dance record, saying \"We are definitely dancing\u2026 I put all my heart, all my pain, all my messages from the other realm that I hear of\u2026 what they tell me to tell the world and I put it into music that I believe to be so fun and you know, energetically really pure. I want people to dance and feel happy. I would like to put out music that a big chunk of the world will hear, and it will become a part of their daily lives and make them happy every single day.\"<ref name=\"Beats1\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/post/sa.e8ad7cc0-59c3-11ea-b990-4d970530bffb|title=Lady Gaga on \"Stupid Love\"|3=|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020|website=New Music Daily with Zane Lowe|publisher=Apple Inc.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229041344/https://music.apple.com/us/post/sa.e8ad7cc0-59c3-11ea-b990-4d970530bffb|archive-date=February 29, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> She divulged how her intuition had evolved since the production of her last album, especially with the \"real\" and \"honest\" nature of this record's production virtually halting her inclination to second guess her creative output.<ref name=\"Beats1\"/> Gaga also went into great detail about how the collaborative process of creating the album helped her overcome her internal struggles:\n{{Quote|text=We made a lot of the record in my studio house. So I have a house where it's [[Frank Zappa|Frank Zappa's]] old [[Utility Muffin Research Kitchen|studio]], it's a live room, it's a big studio, it's beautiful. And I would be upstairs on the porch, outside the kitchen, and Bloodpop would come up and he'd go, 'Okay, come on, that's enough, off the porch,' and I would cry and I would say, 'I'm miserable, I'm sad, I\u2019m depressed,' and he'd go, 'I know, and we're gonna go make some music now. And then I'd go downstairs and I would write. This album is such a display of not only how you can reframe the way that you view the world, but I promise and I hope, that the love that was around me in the process of making this album is something that other people feel, that they know that artistically, like, you know how producers are, if one guy\u2019s working on it, or one girl\u2019s working on it, they don\u2019t want anyone else to work on it, they don\u2019t wanna share, they, everybody gets cocky, there was none of that. These records got passed around to so many different people, there were so many different iterations of these songs because we all wanted it to be perfect and literally nobody cared who put their fingerprints on it, as long as it was the dopest thing that we could give to the world and that it was meaningful, authentic, and completely me.<ref name=\"Beats1\"/>}}\n\nIn an interview with ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'' released in March 2020, Gaga talked at length about numerous topics, including the recording process for ''Chromatica'', and confirmed that BloodPop was the \"center\" and her \"nucleus\" of production while creating the album and that he had a hand in the creation of every track.<ref name=\"Paper1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/lady-gaga-chromatica-2645479910.html |title=Lady Gaga: Life on Chromatica |last=Moran |first=Justin |date=March 16, 2020 |accessdate=March 20, 2020 |work=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]}}</ref> It was also confirmed in the same interview that Gaga worked with a wide array of producers and musicians, such as [[Burns (musician)|Burns]], [[Axwell]] of [[Swedish House Mafia]], [[Tchami]], Benjamin Rice, and [[Rami Yacoub]], to create an album described as an \"[[electronic music|electronic]] [[tapestry]]\u201d by the interviewer.<ref name=\"Paper1\"/> In discussing the large collaborative atmosphere that enveloped the album's production, she said, \"It's easy to go into a computer and find a cool loop, but the producers I work with don't work this way. When they're inspired, they embroider things.\"<ref name=\"Paper1\"/> Gaga disclosed that she had collaborated with a \"fellow female pop star who [had similarly experienced] immense trauma while in the public eye\" and went into depth about the genesis of their song, which she describes as a \"celebration of all the tears\": \"I sat with her and we talked about our lives. It's two women having a conversation about how to keep going and how to be grateful for what you do.\"<ref name=\"Paper1\"/>\n\n==Title and packaging==\nTalking about the album's title, Gaga stated \"I live on Chromatica, that is where I live. I went into my frame. I found earth, I deleted it. Earth is canceled. I live on Chromatica.\" A temporary cover art was released along with the album preorder, showcasing a symbol which \"has a [[sine wave]] in it, which is the mathematical symbol for sound. And, for me, sound is what healed me in my life period, and it healed me again making this record, and that is really what Chromatica is all about.\"<ref name=\"Pitchfork2020\">{{cite web |title=Lady Gaga Announces New Album Chromatica |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/lady-gaga-announces-new-album-chromatica/ |last1=Strauss |first1=Matthew |last2=Bloom |first2=Matthew |date=March 2, 2020 |accessdate=March 2, 2020 |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302173858/https://pitchfork.com/news/lady-gaga-announces-new-album-chromatica/ |archive-date=March 2, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nGaga also confirmed how the concept of the planet Chromatica came about, saying: <blockquote>BloodPop brought it up, and we talked about how Chromatica was essentially on its own when you first look at it, it seems to be about colors and all the different colors and also music is made of a [[chromatic scale]], you know? So it's all the colors, all the sounds, you know, so we, we're talking about inclusivity and life and also a lot of what we see around us and what we're experiencing is math, which is very much like music and sound is math as well. So we talked about that, and then I sort of went back and I said, 'OK, well, yeah, it's inclusivity but it's really a way of thinking,' you know, it's not just, 'Oh, Chromatica, we're being inclusive with all the colors, all the people,' and when I say, 'All the colors, all the people'  I mean way more than we could possibly fathom.\"<ref name=\"Pitchfork2020\"/></blockquote>\n\nOn April 5, 2020, the album's official cover was revealed.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=ladygaga |number=1246905802952077312 |title=#Chromatica \u2694\ufe0f\ud83d\udc932020 |date=April 5, 2020 |accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> It shows the singer with \"cotton candy pink\" hair, wearing a \"metallic bodysuit with spikes and studs sticking out of it\", \"a pair of platform boots with a tusk and a knife for its heels\" and a \"shoulder-to-fingertip sleeve covered in spikes\" on one of her hands. She is attached to a large metal grate illuminated by \"hot pink neon\" light.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daly |first1=Rhian |title=Lady Gaga shares first look at 'Chromatica' album artwork |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-shares-first-look-at-chromatica-album-artwork-2641331 |website=[[NME]] |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |date=April 6, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Lady Gaga Unveils The Mind-Boggling Cover Of 'Chromatica' |url=https://www.idolator.com/7908903/lady-gaga-unveils-the-mind-boggling-cover-of-chromatica?view-all&adblock=1&chrome=1 |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |date=April 5, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hughes |first1=Hilary |title=Lady Gaga Flexes Her 'Chromatica' Claws in New Album Cover Art: See the Pics |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9351515/lady-gaga-chromatica-album-cover-art |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=April 6, 2020 |date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Release and promotion==\nIn response to tabloid reports saying she might be pregnant, Gaga tweeted on March 12, 2019, \"Rumors I'm pregnant? Yeah, I'm pregnant with #LG6.\"<ref>{{cite tweet |user=ladygaga |number=1105619299572432897 |date=March 12, 2019 |title=Rumors I\u2019m pregnant? Yeah, I\u2019m pregnant with #LG6 }}</ref><ref name=\"LG6\">{{cite web|last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Lady Gaga Confirms That She\u2019s Hard At Work On \u2018LG6\u2019 |work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=March 13, 2019 |url=https://www.idolator.com/7721307/lady-gaga-new-album-2019-lg6 |accessdate=March 18, 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Maicki |first1=Salvatore |title=Lady Gaga says she\u2019s pregnant with her new album |work=[[The Fader]] |date=March 12, 2019 |url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/03/12/lady-gaga-new-album-lg6-rumors-rihanna-instagram |accessdate=March 18, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330062430/https://www.thefader.com/2019/03/12/lady-gaga-new-album-lg6-rumors-rihanna-instagram |archive-date=March 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Several news outlets speculated the tweet alluded to a release within a nine month window, the typical span of a human pregnancy, but the anniversary has since come and gone, proving the theory to be false.<ref name=\"LG6\"/> In October 2019, she jokingly announced via Twitter that the album would be called ''Adele'' after the [[Adele|English singer-songwriter of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.avclub.com/move-over-joanne-cause-lady-gaga-says-her-next-albums-1838678026 |last=Vargas |first=Alani |date=October 1, 2019 |accessdate=November 10, 2019 |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |title=Move Over ''Joanne'', 'Cause Lady Gaga Says her Next Album's Called...''Adele'' |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107094014/https://news.avclub.com/move-over-joanne-cause-lady-gaga-says-her-next-albums-1838678026 |archive-date=November 7, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/10/lady-gagas-sixth-album-will-be-called-adele.html|title=Trolling in the Deep: Lady Gaga's Calling Her Next Album ADELE|website=[[Vulture (website)|Vulture]]|last=Alter|first=Rebecca|date=October 1, 2019|accessdate=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122025553/https://www.vulture.com/2019/10/lady-gagas-sixth-album-will-be-called-adele.html|archive-date=November 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-naming-next-album-adele-2552838|title=Is Lady Gaga naming her next album 'ADELE'?|work=[[NME]]|last=Clarke|first=Patrick|date=October 1, 2019|accessdate=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002200058/https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-naming-next-album-adele-2552838|archive-date=October 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2020, several news outlets reported that the album's lead single was scheduled to be released in early February, with the album's release following soon afterwards.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Close |first1=Paris |title=Lady Gaga Will Reportedly Release A New Song In February |work=[[iHeartRadio]] |url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2020-01-19-lady-gaga-will-reportedly-release-a-new-song-in-february/ |date=January 19, 2020 |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200120015830/https://www.iheart.com/content/2020-01-19-lady-gaga-will-reportedly-release-a-new-song-in-february/ |archive-date=January 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n\nOn March 2, 2020, Gaga announced that the album is named ''Chromatica'' and that it will be released on April 10, 2020. The pre-order for the album was made available with the announcement.<ref name=\"Stereogum\"/><ref name=\"Fader\"/> On March 24, Gaga announced in a statement on Instagram and other platforms that the release would be postponed until later that year due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9341556/lady-gaga-pushes-back-chromatica-album |last1=Hughes |first1=Hilary |title=Lady Gaga Pushes Back 'Chromatica' Album Due to 'All That Is Going On' With Global Pandemic |date=March 24, 2020 |access-date=March 25, 2020 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref>\n<!-- Don\u2019t add the tour here, create a separate page for \"The Chromatica Ball\". -->\n\n===Singles===\n\"[[Stupid Love (Lady Gaga song)|Stupid Love]]\" was released as the album's [[lead single]] on February 28, 2020.<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/lady-gaga-stupid-love-new-single-leak-1203474728/|title=Lady Gaga\u2019s New Single, \u2018Stupid Love,\u2019 Is Dropping Friday|last=Stedman|first=Alex|last2=|first2=|date=2020-02-25|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225171654/https://variety.com/2020/music/news/lady-gaga-stupid-love-new-single-leak-1203474728/|archive-date=February 25, 2020|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The accompanying music video was directed by [[Daniel Askill]] and was released alongside the song on February 28.\n\n===Tour===\n{{main|The Chromatica Ball}}\nOn March 5, 2020, Gaga announced she would embark on [[The Chromatica Ball]] tour to support the album.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9328728/lady-gaga-sets-chromatica-stadium-tour |title=Lady Gaga Sets &#39;Chromatica&#39; Stadium Tour |date=March 5, 2020 |access-date=March 5, 2020 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref><ref name=\"RollingStone\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/lady-gaga-chromatica-ball-tour-962547/ |title=Lady Gaga Announces Six-City The Chromatica Ball Summer Tour |date=March 5, 2020 |access-date=March 5, 2020 |website=[[Rolling Stone]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Variety2\">{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/lady-gaga-chromatica-ball-tour-dates-1203524722/ |title=Lady Gaga Unveils \u2018Chromatica Ball\u2019 Tour Dates |date=March 5, 2020 |access-date=March 5, 2020 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> The six-date trek is scheduled to begin on July 24, 2020, in [[Saint-Denis, Seine-Saint-Denis|Saint-Denis]], France and end on August 19, 2020, in [[East Rutherford, New Jersey|East Rutherford]], United States.<ref name=\"Gaga.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ladygaga.com/thechromaticaball|title=LADY GAGA {{!}} THE CHROMATICA BALL|date=March 5, 2020|website=LADY GAGA|language=en|access-date=March 5, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"RollingStone\"/><ref name=\"Variety2\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\nIt is revealed the album will contain 16 tracks in total, while the [[Target Corporation|Target]]-exclusive deluxe edition will contain three additional tracks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/chromatica/1500951604|title=Chromatica by Lady Gaga on Apple Music|date=April 10, 2020|author=Lady Gaga|website=music.apple.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.target.com/p/lady-gaga-chromatica-target-exclusive-cd/-/A-79694377|title=Lady Gaga - Chromatica (Target Exclusive, CD)|website=www.target.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| total_length = \n| title1 = \n| writer1 = \n| extra1 = \n| length1 = \n| title2 = \n| writer2 = \n| extra2 = \n| length2 = \n| title3 = [[Stupid Love (Lady Gaga song)|Stupid Love]]\n| writer3 = {{hlist|[[Lady Gaga|Stefani Germanotta]]|[[Max Martin]]|Ely Weisfeld|[[BloodPop|Michael Tucker]]|[[Tchami|Martin Bresso]]}}\n| extra3 = {{hlist|[[BloodPop]]|[[Tchami]]|Martin{{ref|b|[b]}}|Ben Rice{{ref|c|[c]}}}}\n| length3 = 3:13\n| title4 =  \n| writer4= \n| extra4= \n| title5 =\n| writer5 =\n| extra5 =\n| length5 = \n| title6 = \n| writer6 = \n| extra6 = \n| length6 = \n| title7 = \n| writer7 = \n| extra7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| writer8 = \n| extra8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| writer9 = \n| extra9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| writer10 = \n| extra10 = \n| length10 = \n| title11 = \n| writer11 = \n| extra11 = \n| length11 = \n| title12 = \n| writer12 = \n| extra12 = \n| length12 = \n| title13 = \n| writer13 = \n| extra13 = \n| length13 = \n| 