{"title_page": "Maquis shrubland", "text_new": "{{Redirect|Macchia}}\n[[image:Macchia01.jpg|thumb|220px|Low maquis in Corsica]]\n[[image:Gutturu mannu g4.jpg|220px|thumb|High ''macchia'' in Sardinia]]\n'''Maquis''' ([[French language|French]]) or '''macchia''' ([[Italian language|Italian]]: ''macchia mediterranea'') is a [[shrubland]] [[biome]] in the [[Mediterranean region]], typically consisting of densely growing [[evergreen]] [[shrub]]s. <ref name=MarCavShrublands>{{cite book|title=Habitats of the world.|date=2006|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|location=New York|isbn=978-0761475231|pages=[https://archive.org/details/isbn_0761475311/page/n11 488], 492\u2013493|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_0761475311|url-access=registration|quote=maquis shrubland.|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=SoilOfItaly>{{cite book|last1=Costantini|first1=Edoardo A.C. (ed.)|last2=Dazzi|first2=Carmelo (ed.)|title=The soils of Italy|date=2013|publisher=Springer|location=Dordrecht|isbn=978-9400756410|pages=30,78,80,83,255,283|url=https://books.google.com/?id=MbhEAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA86&dq=macchia+degradation#v=onepage&q=macchia%20erosion&f=false|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref>\u00b8\n\nThis biome gave its name to the [[Maquis (World War II)|''maquis'']] resistance movement in World War II France, the implication being that its members had \"taken to the bush.\"\n\n==See also==\n* [[Garrigue]] \n* [[Maquis (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Mediterranean forests, woodlands, and scrub]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commons category-inline|Maquis shrubland}}\n* {{Commons category-inline|Maquis (vegetation)}}\n* {{Commonscat-inline|Mediterranean forests, woodlands, and scrub}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maquis Shrubland}}\n[[Category:Matorral shrubland|*]]\n[[Category:Ecoregions of Europe]]\n[[Category:Ecoregions of Metropolitan France]]\n[[Category:Environment of the Mediterranean]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean forests, woodlands, and scrub]]\n[[Category:Palearctic ecoregions]]\n[[Category:Subshrubs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|Macchia}}\n[[image:Macchia01.jpg|thumb|220px|Low maquis in Corsica]]\n[[image:Gutturu mannu g4.jpg|220px|thumb|High ''macchia'' in Sardinia]]\n'''Maquis''' ([[French language|French]]) or '''macchia''' ([[Italian language|Italian]]: ''macchia mediterranea'') is a [[shrubland]] [[biome]] in the [[Mediterranean region]], typically consisting of densely growing [[evergreen]] [[shrub]]s. <ref name=MarCavShrublands>{{cite book|title=Habitats of the world.|date=2006|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|location=New York|isbn=978-0761475231|pages=[https://archive.org/details/isbn_0761475311/page/n11 488], 492\u2013493|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_0761475311|url-access=registration|quote=maquis shrubland.|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref><ref name=SoilOfItaly>{{cite book|last1=Costantini|first1=Edoardo A.C. (ed.)|last2=Dazzi|first2=Carmelo (ed.)|title=The soils of Italy|date=2013|publisher=Springer|location=Dordrecht|isbn=978-9400756410|pages=30,78,80,83,255,283|url=https://books.google.com/?id=MbhEAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA86&dq=macchia+degradation#v=onepage&q=macchia%20erosion&f=false|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Garrigue]] \n* [[Maquis (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Mediterranean forests, woodlands, and scrub]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commons category-inline|Maquis shrubland}}\n* {{Commons category-inline|Maquis (vegetation)}}\n* {{Commonscat-inline|Mediterranean forests, woodlands, and scrub}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maquis Shrubland}}\n[[Category:Matorral shrubland|*]]\n[[Category:Ecoregions of Europe]]\n[[Category:Ecoregions of Metropolitan France]]\n[[Category:Environment of the Mediterranean]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean forests, woodlands, and scrub]]\n[[Category:Palearctic ecoregions]]\n[[Category:Subshrubs]]\n", "name_user": "76.64.243.206", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maquis_shrubland"}
